for_sales.sales_text:
"Etoile Manureva" is a French cutter, lying in Roscoff, France. She is offered for sale to a new custodian with a passion for beautiful wooden boats. 

Built at le Havre in 1947, she sailed for many years before having a Vetus engine fitted in 2013..

Contact Jean Yvon Combot, a member of the French OGA for more details.
for_sales.summary: Built at le Havre, 1947 and now lying Roscoff, France, "Manureva" seeks a new custodian with a passion for beautiful wooden boats.
